---
import TableOfContents from "@/components/TableOfContents";
import DashboardLayout from "@/layouts/DashboardLayout.astro";
import Header from "@/layouts/Header.astro";

const imageWidth = 400;
const sectionClass = "flex scroll-mt-4 flex-col gap-4";
const textClass = "text-foreground/80 leading-relaxed";
const imgClass = "self-center rounded-lg";
const codeClass = "rounded-md bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs";
const h3Class = "font-medium text-lg";
const dividerClass = "border-t border-border/40";
---

<DashboardLayout title="Tips & Tricks">
  <div
    class="container relative mx-auto flex w-full max-w-2xl flex-col gap-8 py-6"
  >
    <Header title="Tips & Tricks" />

    <div class="border-t border-border/50"></div>
    <TableOfContents />
    <div class="border-t border-border/50 lg:hidden"></div>

    <section id="proxies" class={sectionClass}>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl">Selecting proxies</h2>
      <p class={textClass}>
        By default, the app will automatically balance proxies for you. However,
        if things feel slow, I recommend choosing the <code class={codeClass}
          >lowest</code
        > balancer option, or manually selecting VLESS or VMESS. Shadowsocks is pretty
        reliable too for tricky sites, but a little bit slower.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/tips/proxy.png"
        alt="proxy"
        width={imageWidth}
        class={imgClass}
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </section>

    <div class={dividerClass}></div>

    <section id="options" class={sectionClass}>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl">DNS settings</h2>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h3 class={h3Class}>Remote DNS</h3>
        <p class={textClass}>
          By default this is set to <code class={codeClass}>local</code>. This
          rarely needs to be changed, but occasionally on public WiFi or 4G/5G
          networks, you can try <code class={codeClass}>tcp://1.1.1.1</code> or <code
            class={codeClass}>tcp://8.8.8.8</code
          >.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h3 class={h3Class}>Outbound/Direct DNS</h3>
        <p class={textClass}>
          <code class={codeClass}>local</code> should always be selected for most
          scenarios. You can try matching this to Remote DNS if all else fails.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h3 class={h3Class}>Fake DNS</h3>
        <p class={textClass}>
          This can be enabled without problems. I find it more reliable with it
          turned on. You can try turning it off if you are having issues.
        </p>
      </div>
      <img
        src="/setup/fake-dns.png"
        width={imageWidth}
        alt="dns config import"
        class={imgClass}
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </section>

    <div class={dividerClass}></div>

    <section id="updates" class={sectionClass}>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl">App updates</h2>
      <p class={textClass}>
        As a last resort, under the About section, you can update the app. It
        should auto-update by itself automatically. Most of the time it's the
        server, a global outage, or during a Chinese holiday or political event.
        Email me if you are having issues for more than a day.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/tips/update.png"
        alt="update"
        width={imageWidth}
        class={imgClass}
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </section>

    <div class={dividerClass}></div>

    <section id="mobile" class={sectionClass}>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl">Mobile tips</h2>
      <p class={textClass}>
        This feature is only available on mobile. Under <strong>Settings</strong
        >
        {" → "}
        <strong>Routing</strong>
        {" → "}
        <strong>Per-App Proxy</strong>. If you have mainly Chinese apps, select <strong
          >Proxy only selected apps</strong
        > and pick foreign apps like Google/Youtube.
      </p>
      <p class={textClass}>
        However, if you mainly have US/international apps, choose <strong
          >Do not proxy selected apps</strong
        > and pick Chinese apps like Alipay/WeChat. This way you can avoid constantly
        turning the VPN on and off.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/tips/per-app.png"
        alt="per-app proxy"
        width={imageWidth}
        class={imgClass}
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </section>
  </div>
</DashboardLayout>
